data.description: Classically beautiful and tastefully modernized brick ranch over fully finished basement on 5 private acres!  Come home to River Ridge, a development of homes on large, wooded estate lots, each one with privacy - especially this one, with trees as far as you can see. A circular driveway provides easy front door access for your guests while a 2-car drive under garage gives you all the covered parking you need.  Step inside the front door to a traditional foyer, off which you can access every area of the home.  Step right into a front and center flex space set off by french doors - office, playroom, or formal living?  You choose.  Continue through to the dedicated dining room and into the eat-in kitchen with exterior back deck access.  This kitchen has the traditional layout that makes preparing meals comfortable, with updated granite counters and modernized cabinets featuring gleaming gold handles, new faucet, under and over cabinet lighting that can emit every color of the rainbow, and don't miss the large pantry, laundry, and half bath just steps away.  A cozy den with gas log fireplace and screened porch access gives you indoor and outdoor living space no matter the season. Travel down the hall, passing by the two amply sized bedrooms which share a full 4-piece hall bath, and end up in the spacious primary suite.  There's no shortage of square footage to accommodate any size bedroom suite or shoe collection - amble through the huge walk in closet and regard the oversized bathroom complete with a garden tub and picture window from which you can survey the completely private acreage.  Notice the motorized window shades?  Those are part of several smart home systems in place. Once you've explored the whole main floor, venture downstairs where you find another 1800+ square feet of house!  This fully finished basement features a huge living space (great for a full size TV or projector set up), wet bar with refrigerator, full bathroom, and 3 rooms: currently being used for a bedroom, a home gym, and an office.  There's also exterior access to the terrace level patio where you can imagine grilling out under the lights that transform the space from utilitarian to ethereal.  This patio area is also wired for a hot tub, and a section of the fence can be removed if you want direct access to your wooded acreage. You can feel good about your investment knowing the primary HVAC system (ACU and condenser) were replaced in 2023, and smart thermostats installed both upstairs and down. When you do find the need to leave this well appointed retreat, you're located just a short distance from nature spaces to explore or cityscapes to search out some excitement.  Commuters and jetsetters will find the Atlanta airport about half an hour away.  Let 6320 River Ridge Drive be the peaceful retreat you look forward to returning home to every time! All information deemed reliable but should be confirmed by buyer.
